Name: Interactive
Description: A user logged on at the computer's console or through Remote Desktop with local credentials.

Name: Network
Description: A user or service accessed the computer over the network (e.g., accessing a shared folder). Credentials are not logged on the local machine. (SMB, RDP)

Name: Batch
Description: Used for scheduled tasks. The Task Scheduler logs on the account when a job runs.

Name: Service
Description: A service started using a service account's credentials.

Name: Unlock
Description: A user unlocked the workstation (e.g., session was locked and then unlocked) and RDP Reconnect.

Name: NetworkCleartext
Description: A user logged on over the network using credentials sent in cleartext (e.g., Basic Authentication).

Name: NewCredentials
Description: A user used RUNAS /netonly or similar to create a logon session with alternate credentials without fully logging in.

Name: RemoteInteractive
Description: A user logged on using Remote Desktop or Remote Assistance (RDP session).

Name: CachedInteractive
Description: A user logged on with cached domain credentials (e.g., logging into a laptop not connected to the domain).

Name: CachedRemoteInteractive
Description: A remote interactive logon (e.g., RDP) using cached credentials when a domain controller is not reachable.

Name: CachedUnlock
Description: A workstation unlock performed using cached credentials while offline from the domain.
